classes.label: CspConfig

classes.label: ExternalUrlConfig
description: External Url configuration for use in Kibana.

signature: { enabled: boolean; allowCredentials: boolean; allowOrigin: string[]; }

children.label: compression
signature: { enabled: boolean; referrerWhitelist?: string[] | undefined; brotli: { enabled: boolean; quality: number; }; }

classes.label: StaticAssets
description: Convention is for trailing slashes in pathnames are stripped.

children.label: getHrefBase
description:
Returns a href (hypertext reference) intended to be used as the base for constructing
other hrefs to static assets.

functions.label: createCookieSessionStorageFactory
description:
Creates SessionStorage factory, which abstract the way of
session storage implementation and scoping to the incoming requests.

children.label: server
description: - hapi server to create SessionStorage for

children.label: isUsingCdn
description:
Returns true if a CDN has been configured and should be used to serve static assets.
Should only be used in scenarios where different behavior has to be used when CDN is enabled or not.

children.label: getPluginAssetHref
description:
Intended for use by server code rendering UI or generating links to static assets
that will ultimately be called from the browser and must respect settings like
serverBasePath

children.label: getPluginServerPath
description:
Intended for use by server code wanting to register static assets against Kibana
as server paths

children.label: prependServerPath
description: Similar to getPluginServerPath, but not plugin-scoped

children.label: prependPublicUrl
description: Will append the given path segment to the configured public path.
